values: Introducing Nintendo Switch, the new home video game system from Nintendo. In addition to providing thrills at home, the Nintendo Switch system can be taken on the go so players can enjoy a full home console experience anytime, anywhere. It's handheld mobility with the power of a home console, with unprecedented new play styles brought to life by the new Joy-Con controllers. The system rests in the Nintendo Switch dock, allowing you to play on a TV in the comfort of your living room. By lifting the Nintendo Switch any time from the dock, the Switch transitions to handheld mode, displaying the game on the touchscreen. The Joy-Con features two analog sticks, a full complement of face and shoulder buttons, built in motion-sensing technology and new HD Rumble. The Joy-Con can be used separately for two player action, inserted into a Joy-Con grip like a traditional controller, held in each hand for left and right controls or attached to either side of the Nintendo Switch.

customerReviews.reviewText: Pretty awesome little gaming console.

This is a great product I love the Nintendo switch I am not and it's in a fanboy I play all consoles and games this is a must have if you are a true gamer




It's everything I expected I know a lot of people saying that the system. Scratches the switch console and it freezes and also have the dead pixels none of those are an issue with my switch

I know any console will have faulty units during launch. I got one of the bad ones. Mine is having major battery issues. It wont charge while powered on and it only last for about an hour while playing Zelda.

Nintendo has once again made a new console that changes everything. I can guarantee you'll see xBox and Playstation imitators soon, Nintendo has created a way to play all your favorite games on your home TV, in bed, on the subway or bus or even in the waiting room of the doctors office. 

It's like carrying an xBox in your pocket and you can play with friends or people around the world. The switch also boasts being a part of the Nintendo family which means you'll be able to play all the Mario games, Zelda, Sonic and any number of Nintendo properties you won't find with an xBox or a Playstation. 

This is a great console for first time gamers or long time Nintendo owners and makes it simple for everyone to enjoy. Let's also not forget that it's just plain gorgeous. The graphics are fantastic and it's as pretty to watch as it is to play. 

If you're in the market for a new game system or if you just like playing Nintendo in general, buy this console now! 

I am writing this review as part of a contest.

customerReviews.reviewTitle: Well thought out, portable and innovative gamepad
customerReviews.reviewText:
I wouldn't consider myself as a hardcore gamer, but would definitely put myself in the serious casual gamer category. I own several of the name brand gaming console and one thing has always remained the same, i.e. the gamepad is fixed, bulky and needs to packed properly. Another biggest problem that I've faced is I've got small hands, and most controllers end up giving me some sort of pain after a considerable amount of gaming. This gamepad is definitely very innovative, where I can use, and my friend with big hands is also able to use it with ease. 
More over the portability is amazing.

Gaming experience is pretty good and definitely a family console my opinion. We had a small gaming session, and it was super fun. Also, the ability to pick up the console and take it with when I'm travelling is really cool. 

All in, it is small, highly portable, very innovative gamepad and can be played anywhere. 

I am writing this review as part of a contest.

I am absolutely in love with this console! From the colors to the portability to the user friendliness, it's an all around great system to have. I've owned it for about 10 days now and I absolutely don't regret my choice. It's so nice to be in the middle of a game and have my family ask to watch tv and be able to snap the joycons on and take it to play in my room instead of fighting over the tv. And I live in a small town and have to drive an hour to get to a bigger city and I love being able to take my switch and entertain myself along the way. Also, my dad and mom live an hour away from each other so it's great to be able to play switch in between houses! I believe everyone will feel like this system caters to their life..because it does! Everyone can have fun with the switch. No matter if you're 8 or 80! Definitely reccomend picking one up yourself!
We had a Nintendo switch for a whole know and its great! Now we have just purchased our second full set for our down stairs family room. The kids love it.

While the Nintendo Switch does not come with a pack in game, which doesn't bother me, the fact that the Switch needs to be both on and have the controllers docked to charge the controllers is quite annoying. 

The battery life of the Switch while undocked isn't that bad, I wish it was a bit longer. The controllers themselves have a very long battery life when fully charged, I had up to around 10 hours of heavy use until they finally died on me. 

I did have an issue with the dock and pack in HDMI cable provided though. Every once in a while the dock would power my Switch on and change to that input while I'm doing other things. So I have to either undock my switch to stop the inputs from changing or turn off the console completely.

One last thing that is cumbersome is that when the Switch is off or asleep, and it is placed onto the dock, it will resume function or turn on again. meaning I have to turn off my system again then place it into the dock while shutting down so it stays off.

Overall I've had a blast with my system and would highly recommend it. These inconveniences are a small matter that don't really detract from my enjoyment of this system.

I bought this for my 6 year old for his Bday. He loooooves it. He plays Fortnite and since its portable, now my 12 year wants one.  He said when he goes to his Gma house he doesn't have to take his xbox one with him. This is a Winner!!

customerReviews.reviewTitle: The Nintendo Switch is REVOLUTIONARY to Gaming
customerReviews.reviewText:
If you're looking for a game console that is a cross-breed between a Nintendo Wii, an iPad and a PS4/Xbox, then you've found just the RIGHT one: the NINTENDO SWITCH. My gaming experience extends pretty far back, so playing the Switch for the first time, I thought to myself how could something be so different, so portable, yet so exciting at the same time? 

It's the the solution for gamers of all ages since you can bring it with you literally everywhere. It's compact and portable so that you can play it at a restaurant or at dinner. In fact, you could even play this at a park! This alone brings a new element to the gaming world; I'll call it revolutionary.

Not only does it have its own screen that you can play while NOT connected to the TV, the graphics on the Switch itself were great. It works hand in hand with the gameplay as the total experience enables players to interact with the game system and each other. Be careful though - the Switch will take attention away from anyone who plays it. It's the ultimate distraction, but deservedly so. I am writing this reviews as part of a contest.
